description: ABOUT OUR DISTURBING IMAGES

The animal abusers are so afraid of the public seeing the truth about how animals are treated that it’s virtually impossible to document the everyday occurrences in animal factories, in laboratories, and in the animal entertainment industry. The people who go undercover to document abuses are unsung HEROS risking life, limb, and liberty to bring the dirty secrets of the animal exploitation industries into public view. TO LOOK AT THE HORRIBLE IMAGES AND VIDEOS IS TO HONOR THEIR WORK!

Because animal suffering is hidden from view in our society- allowing the offenders to continue their abuse behind closed doors- watching the brutal images and videos remind us why we were moved to boycott violence against animals in the first place.

The worst thing we can do to the animal abusers and the best thing we can do for the animals is to BEAR WITNESS TO THE ABUSES AND DOCUMENT THEM FOR OTHERS TO SEE. THE POWER OF THE IMAGES AND VIDIOS CAN’T BE DIMINISHED, AND THE TRUTH OF IT CAN’T BE DENIED! WE ARE THEIR VOICE!

